<subSubSection id="91E06561FFC30D24FA51F43BF7C6F3EB" pageId="4" pageNumber="459" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="D94536EAFFC30D24FA51F43BF7C6F3EB" blockId="4.[1412,2618,2512,3167]" pageId="4" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="EB8EEAF8FFC30D24FA51F43BF955F434" bold="true" box="[1414,1762,3015,3048]" pageId="4" pageNumber="459">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The [UCN Red List. Coastal Atlantic Forest in north-eastern Brazil has been heavily degraded, which might suggest that Iack’s Redrumped 
<taxonomicName id="1EFA4D69FFC30D24FA28F3EAF9EBF3EB" box="[1535,1628,3094,3127]" class="Mammalia" family="Cuniculidae" genus="Agouti" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="4" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Agouti</taxonomicName>
faces significant conservation threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
